{
  "stem": "14060.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "Right, now, coming back after Austria, the next event which we were well aware of was when-- after Chamberlain's appeasement in Munich, the Germans went into Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "The reason for it is that my mother's-- one, two, three brothers out of four, all married from Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "Czechoslovakia was one of the most prosperous countries before the war and had one of the best products.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "Its Jewish community is longstanding, going back Prague and so on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And I remember vividly that my oldest uncle-- he wasn't the oldest of the brothers and sisters, but the oldest brother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "His name was Alexander Holzer.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "His in-laws suddenly appeared in [NON-ENGLISH] as soon as the Germans came in in '39.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "A very nice elderly couple who were large agricultural landowners came and lived with my uncle and aunt and their daughter there all the years-- very nice, gentle people.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And that gave me the impression what was going on in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "But obviously, part of Slovakia then, under the 1940 Vienna treaty, was passed on to Hungary.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And basically, the Czechoslovak jury, those who were not annexed to, to, to Hungary, had an easy way to-- because they spoke mostly Hungarian, as well-- to come over to Hungary between the years of '39 and '44.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "But they've already-- and they lived as non-Jews and with-- or with Jewish families, depending on what papers they had.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And really, they were already better equipped when it came to the 1944 troubles in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "They ran back to Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "And they went into bunkers in hiding because they were already under this constant threat of being caught-- already for, for, for, for, four or five years, from '39 to '44.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "Anyway, it's interesting to note that-- how rampant the anti-Semitism in, in Slovakia was.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
